Arthur A. MAYERS, Appellant, v. MASSACHUSETTS MUTUAL LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY, Respondent. No. 407. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 6, 1935. I, Jack London, of New York City (Jay Leo Rothschild, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Cabell, Ignatius, Lown & Blinken, of New York City (James M. Lown and Joseph S. Catalano, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed on opinion below (11 F. Supp. 80).
